VU olume, intensity and frequency are what actually form the foundation of programs. 
These three variables are interrelated and inseparable from each other. Each 
affects the other and can do so in different contexts. 
> If you train at a very high intensity of effort, near to failure, it takes longer for 
muscle damage to subside (exercise-induced muscle damage is the normal, easily 
repaired disruption to the fiber as a result of high tension or high volumes; in excess 
it interferes with performance and adaptation) and performance to recover back to 
