Step 4: Exercise Selection 
For a bodybuilder or hypertrophy-focused trainee, you can slot in various exercises to fill 
the weekly muscle group volume goals. If you view the following table you can see which 
muscle groups a given exercise “counts” for. 
As it currently stands, we know an exercise that trains a muscle group indirectly (labeled 
‘'secondary') probably doesn’t provide quite as much stimulus to the muscle as some- 
thing that trains it directly (labeled 'primary'), but the scientific data up to this point has 
counted secondary and primary muscle group volume the same. So, count everything 
on a one to one basis for each muscle group, just be aware that you don’t want all your 
volume for a given muscle group coming from indirect work. 
Quads, Glutes 
Squat (all variations, leg press, 
Erectors Cif free 
